---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Live in the Word | Makor"
  description="Read and study the whole Bible in one, two, three, or four years. Put the big rocks in first, and let Scripture become the place you live."
>
  <div class="plan-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">A reading plan</p>
      <h1>Live in the Word</h1>
      <p class="lead">Read and study the whole Bible, one sitting at a time, until Scripture is not a place you visit but a place you live.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="plan-section" id="myplan" hidden>
      <h2>Your plan</h2>
      <p id="mp-summary"></p>
      <div class="mp-today" id="mp-today"></div>
      <div class="mp-progress">
        <div class="mp-bar"><i id="mp-fill"></i></div>
        <span id="mp-count"></span>
      </div>
      <p class="mp-note" id="mp-note"></p>
      <p class="mp-actions">
        <button id="mp-sync" class="mp-btn" type="button">Check for new studies</button>
        <button id="mp-change" class="mp-btn alt2" type="button">Change my plan</button>
        <button id="mp-about" class="mp-btn alt2" type="button">About this plan</button>
      </p>
      <p class="gstatus" id="gstatus2" hidden></p>
    </section>

    <section class="plan-section plan-intro">
      <h2>Put the big rocks in first</h2>
      <p class="plead">There is an old picture of a jar. If you fill it first with sand and small pebbles, the big rocks never fit. But put the big rocks in first, and the sand and pebbles settle into the space around them. The jar holds everything.</p>
      <p>Time in God's Word is a big rock. Left to the leftover minutes of a day, it is the first thing crowded out by sand. So this plan does one simple thing: it puts the rock in first. It places your time in Scripture on your calendar, at hours you choose, before the day fills up. Not another thing to feel behind on. A fixed point the rest of your life can order itself around.</p>
      <div class="rocks">
        <p style="margin:0">The aim is not to finish a book. It is to be formed by One. Reading the whole Bible is simply what happens along the way, when you keep showing up to the fountain.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="plan-section plan-intro">
      <h2>Why the number four matters</h2>
      <p>This is not only a good idea; it is a measured one. Over eight years the Center for Bible Engagement studied more than a hundred thousand people, asking a plain question: what difference does time in the Bible actually make?</p>
      <p>The answer surprised even the researchers. Reading Scripture once, twice, even three times a week made almost no measurable difference in a person's life. The line stayed flat. But at four times a week, something changed sharply.</p>
      <div class="stat">At four or more days a week, the effect spiked: markedly less given to anger, addiction, and despair, markedly more likely to share their faith and to grow. They named it the Power of 4, and called frequent time in the Word the single strongest predictor of spiritual growth.</div>
      <p class="src">Center for Bible Engagement, <i>Understanding the Bible Engagement Challenge: Scientific Evidence for the Power of 4</i> (2009), now the research arm of Our Daily Bread Ministries.</p>
      <p>Three days a week leaves you roughly where you started. Four days a week changes you. Every plan below is built to carry you past that line without your having to think about it, because the rhythm is already on your calendar.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="plan-section" id="builder-section">
      <h2 class="plan-intro">Choose your plan</h2>
      <p class="plan-intro" style="margin-bottom:6px">Pick how you want to move through the Bible, how long you want to take, how often you want to sit, and the times of day that fit your life. We will build a calendar you can add to Google Calendar, Apple Calendar, or Outlook in one step. Each entry names the passage, sums up the study, and links straight to it.</p>

      <div class="builder">
        <h2 class="builder-h">Build your calendar</h2>

        <div class="step">
          <label class="h">1 · Reading order</label>
          <div class="opts" id="order">
            <div class="opt sel" data-order="multitrack"><span class="rec">Recommended</span>Multi-track<small>a little from several parts each day</small></div>
            <div class="opt" data-order="canonical">Canonical<small>Genesis to Revelation, in order</small></div>
            <div class="opt" data-order="chronological">Chronological<small>in the order events happened</small></div>
          </div>
          <p class="explain" id="orderExplain"></p>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <label class="h">2 · How long</label>
          <div class="opts" id="years">
            <div class="opt sel" data-years="1"><span class="rec">Recommended</span>1 year<small>the deep dive</small></div>
            <div class="opt" data-years="2">2 years<small>steady</small></div>
            <div class="opt" data-years="3">3 years<small>gentle</small></div>
            <div class="opt" data-years="4">4 years<small>one a day</small></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <label class="h">3 · How often</label>
          <div class="opts" id="cadence">
            <div class="opt sel" data-cadence="daily"><span class="rec">Recommended</span>Every day<small>seven days a week</small></div>
            <div class="opt" data-cadence="weekday">Weekdays<small>Monday to Friday</small></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <label class="h">4 · Your sittings</label>
          <div class="slot" data-slot="1">
            <input type="checkbox" checked>
            <div class="name"><b>Morning</b><small>any time from midnight to 8am</small></div>
            <input type="time" value="05:00" min="00:00" max="07:59">
          </div>
          <div class="slot off" data-slot="2">
            <input type="checkbox">
            <div class="name"><b>Midday</b><small>any time from 8am to 4pm</small></div>
            <input type="time" value="13:00" min="08:00" max="15:59">
          </div>
          <div class="slot off" data-slot="3">
            <input type="checkbox">
            <div class="name"><b>Evening</b><small>any time from 4pm to midnight</small></div>
            <input type="time" value="18:00" min="16:00" max="23:59">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label>Start date</label>
            <input type="date" id="start">
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="summary" id="summary"></div>
        <div class="banner" id="banner" style="display:none"></div>

        <button class="go" id="gcal">Add to my Google Calendar</button>
        <p class="gstatus" id="gstatus" hidden></p>
        <button class="go alt" id="go">Download a calendar file (.ics) instead</button>
        <p class="note">The Google button signs you in and places the plan in its own "Makor reading plan" calendar; Makor only receives permission to manage calendars it creates, never your existing ones, and you can remove the whole plan any time by deleting that calendar. As new studies are published, press the button again and we will add them. The file download works with Apple Calendar, Outlook, and Google Calendar (Settings, then Import and export); it is yours to change or remove.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .plan-page .plan-section { border-top: 1px solid var(--line); padding: 1.9rem 0; }
  .plan-page .hero + .plan-section { border-top: 0; }
  .plan-page h2 { font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 0 0 0.7rem; }
  .plan-page p { font-size: 1rem; margin: 0 0 0.9rem; }
  .plan-page .plead { font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .plan-page .rocks { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.3rem 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .plan-page .stat { border-left: 3px solid var(--light); padding: 0.3rem 0 0.3rem 1.1rem; margin: 1.2rem 0; font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--ink); }
  .plan-page .src { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 0.4rem; }

  /* builder card */
  .plan-page .builder { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.6rem 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.6rem; box-shadow: 0 24px 55px -38px rgba(14,42,46,.45); }
  .plan-page .builder-h { font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .plan-page .builder .step { margin: 1.3rem 0; }
  .plan-page .builder label.h { display: block; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.74rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--light); margin-bottom: 0.65rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .plan-page .opts { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; }
  .plan-page .opt { flex: 1 1 120px; border: 1px solid var(--line); background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink); border-radius: 10px; padding: 14px 12px; text-align: center; cursor: pointer; font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1rem; transition: .15s; position: relative; }
  .plan-page .opt small { display: block; font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 4px; }
  .plan-page .opt.sel { background: var(--water); border-color: var(--water); color: #fff; }
  .plan-page .opt.sel small { color: #dff0ee; }
  .plan-page .rec { position: absolute; top: -9px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); background: var(--light); color: #fff; font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 20px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .plan-page .explain { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 0.7rem; line-height: 1.55; }
  .plan-page .slot { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 12px 14px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .plan-page .slot .name { flex: 1; }
  .plan-page .slot .name b { font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--ink); }
  .plan-page .slot .name small { display: block; color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.74rem; }
  .plan-page .slot input[type=time] { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--ink); border-radius: 7px; padding: 8px 10px; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .plan-page .slot input[type=checkbox] { width: 20px; height: 20px; accent-color: var(--water); }
  .plan-page .slot.off { opacity: .55; }
  .plan-page .summary { background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1rem 1.15rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--ink); }
  .plan-page .summary b { color: var(--water); font-family: var(--serif); }
  .plan-page .go { display: block; width: 100%; background: var(--light); color: #fff; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px; font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.1rem; cursor: pointer; margin-top: 1.1rem; }
  .plan-page .go:hover { filter: brightness(1.05); }
  .plan-page .go.alt { background: transparent; color: var(--water); border: 1px solid var(--line); font-weight: 500; font-size: 0.95rem; padding: 12px; margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .plan-page .gstatus { background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-left: 3px solid var(--water); border-radius: 8px; padding: 10px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--ink); margin-top: 0.9rem; }
  .plan-page .note { font-size: 0.76rem; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.5; }
  .plan-page .banner { background: var(--light-soft); border: 1px solid #ecdcae; color: #8a6d1f; border-radius: 8px; padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 0.8rem; margin-top: 0.9rem; }
  .plan-page .field { margin-top: 0.85rem; }
  .plan-page .field label { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .plan-page .field input[type=date] { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--ink); border-radius: 7px; padding: 9px 11px; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.9rem; width: 100%; max-width: 220px; }

  /* your plan card */
  .plan-page #myplan { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.5rem 1.5rem 1.2rem; margin-top: 1.2rem; box-shadow: 0 24px 55px -38px rgba(14,42,46,.45); }
  .plan-page #myplan h2 { margin-top: 0; }
  .plan-page .mp-today { background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-left: 3px solid var(--light); border-radius: 10px; padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem; margin: 0.8rem 0; }
  .plan-page .mp-today .mp-label { display: block; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--light); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .plan-page .mp-today a { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.1rem; }
  .plan-page .mp-today .mp-sum { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0.25rem 0 0; }
  .plan-page .mp-progress { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.8rem; margin: 0.9rem 0 0.2rem; }
  .plan-page .mp-bar { flex: 1; height: 8px; background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; }
  .plan-page .mp-bar i { display: block; height: 100%; background: var(--water); width: 0; }
  .plan-page .mp-progress span { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--muted); white-space: nowrap; }
  .plan-page .mp-note { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .plan-page .mp-actions { margin: 0.9rem 0 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .plan-page .mp-btn { background: var(--water); color: #fff; border: 0; border-radius: 8px; padding: 9px 14px; font-family: inherit; font-size: 0.85rem; cursor: pointer; }
  .plan-page .mp-btn.alt2 { background: transparent; color: var(--water); border: 1px solid var(--line); }
</style>

<script is:inline>
/*
  Publish one ordered index per reading order (array order = reading order):
    /plan-index-multitrack.json  (default)   /plan-index-canonical.json   /plan-index-chronological.json
  Item: { "title","ref","summary","url" }
*/
var WHOLE_BIBLE = 1354;      // total movements in Scripture; the plan paces to finish these
var COMMITTED_HINT = 817;    // studies committed so far (fallback until the index loads)
var SAMPLE = [
  {title:"The Seven Days", ref:"Genesis 1:1-2:3", summary:"God speaks a formless void into an ordered, good, and habitable home.", url:"https://makor.co.za/genesis/the-seven-days/"},
  {title:"The Word Became Flesh", ref:"John 1:1-18", summary:"The One who spoke creation is given a name and a face.", url:"https://makor.co.za/john/the-word-became-flesh/"},
  {title:"The Prophet's Grief and Hope", ref:"Lamentations 3:22-23", summary:"From the ashes of a fallen city, mercy new every morning.", url:"https://makor.co.za/lamentations/the-prophets-grief-and-hope/"}
];
var ORDER_TEXT = {
  multitrack:"You walk in several parts of the Bible at once: an Old Testament story, a Gospel, a Psalm, a letter. Every day is a feast rather than a long march through one book. This is how most people who finish actually finish.",
  canonical:"Straight through, Genesis to Revelation, in the Bible's own order. Simple and complete, though it holds you in the long books before you reach the Gospels.",
  chronological:"In the rough order the events happened, so history reads as a single unfolding story from creation to the church."
};
var SLOT_NAME = {1:'morning',2:'midday',3:'evening'};
var SLOT_TIME_DEFAULT = {1:'05:00',2:'13:00',3:'18:00'};
var PRIORITY = [1,3,2]; // morning first, then evening, then midday
var studies = SAMPLE.slice();
var indexLoaded = false;
var state = {order:'multitrack', years:1, cadence:'daily', slots:{1:{on:true},2:{on:false},3:{on:false}}};

function loadIndex(){
  fetch('/plan-index-'+state.order+'.json').then(function(r){return r.json();}).then(function(d){
    if(Array.isArray(d) && d.length){ studies=d; indexLoaded=true; } else { studies=SAMPLE; indexLoaded=false; }
    render();
  }).catch(function(){ studies=SAMPLE; indexLoaded=false; render(); });
}

// how many sittings a duration needs, in priority order (morning, evening, midday)
function slotsForYears(y){ if(y===1)return [1,3,2]; if(y===2)return [1,3]; return [1]; }
function autoSelectSlots(){
  var want=slotsForYears(state.years);
  [1,2,3].forEach(function(s){
    var on=want.indexOf(s)>=0;
    state.slots[s].on=on;
    var el=document.querySelector('.slot[data-slot="'+s+'"]');
    el.querySelector('input[type=checkbox]').checked=on;
    el.classList.toggle('off',!on);
  });
}

function activePerYear(){ return state.cadence==='weekday'?261:365; }
function ratePerDay(){ return WHOLE_BIBLE/(activePerYear()*state.years); }
function enabledOrdered(){ return PRIORITY.filter(function(s){return state.slots[s].on;}); }
function distribute(n,slotsOrdered){ var S=slotsOrdered.length, base=Math.floor(n/S), rem=n%S, out={};
  slotsOrdered.forEach(function(s,i){ out[s]=base+(i<rem?1:0); }); return out; }

function pad(n){ return String(n).padStart(2,'0'); }
function fmt(d){ return d.getFullYear()+pad(d.getMonth()+1)+pad(d.getDate())+'T'+pad(d.getHours())+pad(d.getMinutes())+'00'; }
function utcstamp(){ var d=new Date(); return d.getUTCFullYear()+pad(d.getUTCMonth()+1)+pad(d.getUTCDate())+'T'+pad(d.getUTCHours())+pad(d.getUTCMinutes())+pad(d.getUTCSeconds())+'Z'; }
function esc(s){ return String(s).replace(/\\/g,'\\\\').replace(/;/g,'\\;').replace(/,/g,'\\,').replace(/\n/g,'\\n'); }
function slotTime(slot){ var el=document.querySelector('.slot[data-slot="'+slot+'"] input[type=time]'); return (el&&el.value)||SLOT_TIME_DEFAULT[slot]; }
function at(d,h,m){ var x=new Date(d); x.setHours(h,m,0,0); return x; }
function addMin(d,mins){ var x=new Date(d); x.setMinutes(x.getMinutes()+mins); return x; }
function commas(n){ return String(n).replace(/\B(?=(\d{3})+(?!\d))/g,','); }

function render(){
  document.getElementById('orderExplain').textContent = ORDER_TEXT[state.order];
  var slotsOrd=enabledOrdered(); if(!slotsOrd.length) slotsOrd=[1];
  var rate=ratePerDay();
  var per = rate>=3.5?'about four':rate>=2.5?'about three':rate>=1.6?'about two':rate>=1.15?'one or two':'about one';
  var sitNames=slotsOrd.map(function(s){return SLOT_NAME[s];}).join(', ');
  var daysWord = state.cadence==='weekday'?'weekday':'day';
  var html='This paces you through all <b>'+commas(WHOLE_BIBLE)+'</b> movements of Scripture in <b>'+state.years+' year'+(state.years>1?'s':'')+'</b>, at <b>'+per+'</b> a '+daysWord+'. ';
  html+='We set your sittings to the <b>'+sitNames+'</b> to suit this pace; adjust any if you like.';
  document.getElementById('summary').innerHTML=html;
  var n=indexLoaded?studies.length:COMMITTED_HINT;
  var b=document.getElementById('banner'); b.style.display='block';
  b.innerHTML='Your calendar will cover the <b>'+commas(n)+'</b> studies committed so far, out of '+commas(WHOLE_BIBLE)+' movements in all. New studies are published continually; with Google Calendar, press the button again any time and we add only what is new. A downloaded file is a snapshot; download again later to extend it.';
}

/* ---------- Your plan: local record and the tracking card ---------- */
function savePlanLocal(cfg){
  try{ localStorage.setItem('makor_plan',JSON.stringify({cfg:cfg,at:Date.now()})); }catch(e){}
  try{ if(window.makorClient&&window.makorUser) window.makorClient.auth.updateUser({data:{makor_plan_cfg:cfg}}); }catch(e){}
}
function loadPlanLocal(){
  try{ return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('makor_plan')||'null'); }catch(e){ return null; }
}
function kebab(s){ return String(s).toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z0-9]+/g,'-').replace(/^-+|-+$/g,''); }
function planKey(url){
  var p=String(url).replace(/^https?:\/\/[^/]+/,'').split('/').filter(Boolean);
  return p.length>=2?(p[0]+'/'+p[1]):url;
}
function escHtml(s){ return String(s).replace(/[&<>"]/g,function(c){return {'&':'&amp;','<':'&lt;','>':'&gt;','"':'&quot;'}[c];}); }
var ORDER_LABEL={multitrack:'Multi-track',canonical:'Canonical',chronological:'Chronological'};

function showPlanCard(cfg){
  var card=document.getElementById('myplan'); if(!card||!cfg) return;
  card.hidden=false;
  document.querySelectorAll('.plan-intro').forEach(function(el){ el.hidden=true; });
  var bs=document.getElementById('builder-section'); if(bs) bs.hidden=true;

  var sitBits=[];
  PRIORITY.slice().sort().forEach(function(s){
    if(cfg.slots&&cfg.slots[s]&&cfg.slots[s].on) sitBits.push(SLOT_NAME[s]+' at '+(cfg.slots[s].time||SLOT_TIME_DEFAULT[s]));
  });
  document.getElementById('mp-summary').textContent=
    (ORDER_LABEL[cfg.order]||cfg.order)+' reading, '+cfg.years+' year'+(cfg.years>1?'s':'')+', '+
    (cfg.cadence==='weekday'?'weekdays':'every day')+', '+sitBits.join(' and ')+
    (cfg.start?', started '+cfg.start:'')+'.';

  fetchIndex(cfg.order).then(function(list){
    var startDay=new Date((cfg.start||new Date().toISOString().slice(0,10))+'T00:00:00');
    var entries=scheduleItems(list,startDay,cfg);
    var attempts=window.makorUser&&window.makorAllAttempts?window.makorAllAttempts():Promise.resolve([]);
    Promise.resolve(attempts).then(function(rows){
      var doneSet={};
      (rows||[]).forEach(function(r){ if(r.phase==='post') doneSet[kebab(r.book)+'/'+r.study_slug]=1; });
      var doneCount=0, next=null;
      list.forEach(function(x){ if(doneSet[planKey(x.url)]) doneCount++; else if(!next) next=x; });

      var today=document.getElementById('mp-today');
      if(window.makorUser&&(rows||[]).length){
        if(next){
          today.innerHTML='<span class="mp-label">Continue where you left off</span>'+
            '<a href="'+escHtml(next.url)+'">'+escHtml(next.title)+(next.ref?' ('+escHtml(next.ref)+')':'')+'</a>'+
            (next.summary?'<p class="mp-sum">'+escHtml(next.summary)+'</p>':'');
        } else {
          today.innerHTML='<span class="mp-label">Well done</span>You have read every committed study. New ones are published continually.';
        }
      } else {
        var now=new Date(); now.setHours(0,0,0,0);
        var todays=entries.filter(function(en){ return en.date.getTime()===now.getTime(); });
        var upcoming=todays.length?todays:entries.filter(function(en){ return en.date.getTime()>now.getTime(); }).slice(0,1);
        var label=todays.length?'Today’s reading':'Next reading';
        if(upcoming.length){
          today.innerHTML='<span class="mp-label">'+label+'</span>'+upcoming.map(function(en){
            return en.items.map(function(x){
              return '<a href="'+escHtml(x.url)+'">'+escHtml(x.title)+(x.ref?' ('+escHtml(x.ref)+')':'')+'</a>';
            }).join('<br>');
          }).join('<br>');
        } else { today.innerHTML='<span class="mp-label">Your plan</span>Your scheduled readings have all passed; press "Check for new studies" to extend the plan.'; }
      }

      var total=list.length, pct=0, countText='';
      if(window.makorUser&&(rows||[]).length){
        pct=total?Math.round(doneCount/total*100):0;
        countText=doneCount+' of '+total+' studies read';
      } else {
        var now2=new Date(); now2.setHours(0,0,0,0);
        var scheduled=0; entries.forEach(function(en){ if(en.date.getTime()<=now2.getTime()) scheduled+=en.items.length; });
        pct=total?Math.round(scheduled/total*100):0;
        countText=scheduled+' of '+total+' studies scheduled so far';
        document.getElementById('mp-note').textContent='Sign in with Google (menu, top right) and complete each study’s quiz to track what you have actually read.';
      }
      document.getElementById('mp-fill').style.width=pct+'%';
      document.getElementById('mp-count').textContent=countText;
    });
  });
}

document.getElementById('mp-sync').onclick=function(){
  var saved=loadPlanLocal();
  gcalRun((saved&&saved.cfg)||cfgFromState());
};
document.getElementById('mp-change').onclick=function(){
  var bs=document.getElementById('builder-section'); if(bs){ bs.hidden=false; bs.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth'}); }
};
document.getElementById('mp-about').onclick=function(){
  document.querySelectorAll('.plan-intro').forEach(function(el){ el.hidden=false; });
  window.scrollTo({top:0,behavior:'smooth'});
};

(function initPlanCard(){
  function boot(){
    var saved=loadPlanLocal();
    if(!saved||!saved.cfg){
      var meta=window.makorUser&&window.makorUser.user_metadata&&window.makorUser.user_metadata.makor_plan_cfg;
      if(meta) saved={cfg:meta};
    }
    if(saved&&saved.cfg) showPlanCard(saved.cfg);
  }
  if(window.makorClient) boot();
  else window.addEventListener('makor-auth',boot,{once:true});
})();

// Each sitting is its own plain event. Recurring events with per-day
// overrides read beautifully on paper, but Google's ICS importer drops
// the overrides and leaves a generic entry with no reading in it, so
// every day carries its full reading explicitly instead.
function build(){
  var stamp=utcstamp();
  var cfg=cfgFromState();
  var startDay=new Date((cfg.start||new Date().toISOString().slice(0,10))+'T00:00:00');
  var lines=['BEGIN:VCALENDAR','VERSION:2.0','PRODID:-//Makor//Reading Plan//EN','CALSCALE:GREGORIAN','METHOD:PUBLISH','X-WR-CALNAME:Makor reading plan'];
  scheduleItems(studies,startDay,cfg).forEach(function(en,i){
    var tm=en.time.split(':');
    var st0=at(en.date,+tm[0],+tm[1]);
    var titles=sittingTitle(en.items);
    var desc=sittingDesc(en.items);
    lines.push('BEGIN:VEVENT');
    lines.push('UID:makor-'+stamp+'-'+i+'@makor.co.za');
    lines.push('DTSTAMP:'+stamp);
    lines.push('DTSTART:'+fmt(st0));
    lines.push('DTEND:'+fmt(addMin(st0,en.items.length>1?55:30)));
    lines.push('SUMMARY:'+esc('Makor: '+titles));
    lines.push('DESCRIPTION:'+esc(desc));
    if(en.items.length===1 && en.items[0].url) lines.push('URL:'+en.items[0].url);
    lines.push('BEGIN:VALARM');lines.push('TRIGGER:-PT10M');lines.push('ACTION:DISPLAY');lines.push('DESCRIPTION:'+esc('Makor: '+titles));lines.push('END:VALARM');
    lines.push('END:VEVENT');
  });
  lines.push('END:VCALENDAR');
  return lines.join('\r\n');
}

document.querySelectorAll('#order .opt').forEach(function(o){ o.onclick=function(){ setSel('#order',o); state.order=o.dataset.order; loadIndex(); }; });
document.querySelectorAll('#years .opt').forEach(function(o){ o.onclick=function(){ setSel('#years',o); state.years=+o.dataset.years; autoSelectSlots(); render(); }; });
document.querySelectorAll('#cadence .opt').forEach(function(o){ o.onclick=function(){ setSel('#cadence',o); state.cadence=o.dataset.cadence; render(); }; });
document.querySelectorAll('.slot').forEach(function(s){ var slot=+s.dataset.slot, cb=s.querySelector('input[type=checkbox]');
  cb.onchange=function(){ state.slots[slot].on=cb.checked; s.classList.toggle('off',!cb.checked); render(); }; });
function setSel(g,el){ document.querySelectorAll(g+' .opt').forEach(function(x){x.classList.remove('sel');}); el.classList.add('sel'); }

var sd=document.getElementById('start'); var t=new Date(); t.setDate(t.getDate()+1); sd.value=t.toISOString().slice(0,10); sd.onchange=render;
document.getElementById('go').onclick=function(){
  var ics=build(); var blob=new Blob([ics],{type:'text/calendar;charset=utf-8'}); var url=URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  var a=document.createElement('a'); a.href=url; a.download='makor-reading-plan.ics'; document.body.appendChild(a); a.click(); document.body.removeChild(a);
  setTimeout(function(){URL.revokeObjectURL(url);},1500);
  var cfg=cfgFromState(); savePlanLocal(cfg); showPlanCard(cfg);
};

autoSelectSlots(); render(); loadIndex();

/* ============================================================
   Google Calendar integration.
   Signs in through the site's existing Supabase Google auth,
   requesting only the calendar.app.created scope: Makor can
   create its own calendar and manage events on it, and can
   never see or touch the user's other calendars.
   The plan lives in a dedicated "Makor reading plan" calendar;
   pressing the button again adds only newly published studies.
   ============================================================ */
var GCAL_SCOPE='https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar.app.created';
var CAL_SUMMARY='Makor reading plan';
var gstatus=document.getElementById('gstatus');
var gstatus2=document.getElementById('gstatus2');

function gsay(msg){
  gstatus.hidden=false; gstatus.textContent=msg;
  if(gstatus2){ gstatus2.hidden=false; gstatus2.textContent=msg; }
}
function userTz(){ try{ return Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone||'Africa/Johannesburg'; }catch(e){ return 'Africa/Johannesburg'; } }
function isoLocal(d){ return d.getFullYear()+'-'+pad(d.getMonth()+1)+'-'+pad(d.getDate())+'T'+pad(d.getHours())+':'+pad(d.getMinutes())+':00'; }

function cfgFromState(){
  return { v:1, order:state.order, years:state.years, cadence:state.cadence,
    slots:{ 1:{on:state.slots[1].on,time:slotTime(1)}, 2:{on:state.slots[2].on,time:slotTime(2)}, 3:{on:state.slots[3].on,time:slotTime(3)} },
    start:document.getElementById('start').value };
}
function applyCfg(cfg){
  try{
    state.order=cfg.order||state.order; state.years=cfg.years||state.years; state.cadence=cfg.cadence||state.cadence;
    [1,2,3].forEach(function(s){
      if(!cfg.slots||!cfg.slots[s]) return;
      state.slots[s].on=!!cfg.slots[s].on;
      var el=document.querySelector('.slot[data-slot="'+s+'"]');
      el.querySelector('input[type=checkbox]').checked=state.slots[s].on;
      el.classList.toggle('off',!state.slots[s].on);
      if(cfg.slots[s].time) el.querySelector('input[type=time]').value=cfg.slots[s].time;
    });
    if(cfg.start) document.getElementById('start').value=cfg.start;
    ['order','years','cadence'].forEach(function(g){
      document.querySelectorAll('#'+g+' .opt').forEach(function(o){
        var v=o.dataset[g==='years'?'years':g]||o.dataset[g];
        o.classList.toggle('sel', String(v)===String(state[g]));
      });
    });
    render(); loadIndex();
  }catch(e){}
}

// Walk a list of studies onto days from startDay at the cfg pace.
// Returns sittings: { date, slot, time, items } in order.
function scheduleItems(list,startDay,cfg){
  var slotsOrd=PRIORITY.filter(function(s){return cfg.slots[s]&&cfg.slots[s].on;}); if(!slotsOrd.length) slotsOrd=[1];
  var perYear=cfg.cadence==='weekday'?261:365;
  var rate=WHOLE_BIBLE/(perYear*(cfg.years||1));
  var idx=0, day=new Date(startDay), acc=0, guard=0, out=[];
  while(idx<list.length && guard<80000){
    guard++;
    var dow=day.getDay();
    if(cfg.cadence==='weekday'&&(dow===0||dow===6)){ day.setDate(day.getDate()+1); continue; }
    acc+=rate; var count=Math.floor(acc+1e-9); acc-=count;
    if(count>0){
      var dist=distribute(count,slotsOrd);
      for(var si=0;si<slotsOrd.length;si++){
        var s=slotsOrd[si];
        var arr=[]; for(var k=0;k<(dist[s]||0)&&idx<list.length;k++) arr.push(list[idx++]);
        if(!arr.length) continue;
        out.push({ date:new Date(day), slot:s, time:(cfg.slots[s].time||SLOT_TIME_DEFAULT[s]), items:arr });
      }
    }
    day.setDate(day.getDate()+1);
  }
  return out;
}

function sittingTitle(arr){ return arr.map(function(x){return x.title+(x.ref?' ('+x.ref+')':'');}).join('  +  '); }
function sittingDesc(arr){
  return arr.map(function(x){
    return 'Read: '+x.title+(x.ref?' ('+x.ref+')':'')+'\n'+(x.summary?x.summary+'\n':'')+x.url;
  }).join('\n\n');
}

// Google event resources, tagged with their study urls so a later
// visit can tell exactly which studies are already on the calendar.
function scheduleEvents(list,startDay,cfg){
  var tz=userTz();
  return scheduleItems(list,startDay,cfg).map(function(en){
    var tm=en.time.split(':');
    var st0=at(en.date,+tm[0],+tm[1]);
    return {
      summary:'Makor: '+sittingTitle(en.items),
      description:sittingDesc(en.items),
      start:{dateTime:isoLocal(st0),timeZone:tz},
      end:{dateTime:isoLocal(addMin(st0,en.items.length>1?55:30)),timeZone:tz},
      reminders:{useDefault:false,overrides:[{method:'popup',minutes:10}]},
      extendedProperties:{private:{makorUrls:en.items.map(function(x){return x.url;}).join(' ')}}
    };
  });
}

function gapi(path,method,body,token){
  return fetch('https://www.googleapis.com/calendar/v3'+path,{
    method:method||'GET',
    headers:{'Authorization':'Bearer '+token,'Content-Type':'application/json'},
    body:body?JSON.stringify(body):undefined
  }).then(function(r){
    if(!r.ok){ var err=new Error('gapi '+r.status); err.status=r.status; throw err; }
    return r.status===204?null:r.json();
  });
}

// Insert events 50 at a time through the Calendar batch endpoint,
// pausing between batches to respect per-user rate limits. A chunk that
// reports errors is retried once; anything still missed is picked up by
// the next "check for new studies" pass, so the plan self-heals.
function gcalBatchInsert(calId,events,token,onProgress){
  var chunks=[]; for(var i=0;i<events.length;i+=50) chunks.push(events.slice(i,i+50));
  var done=0;
  function send(ci,attempt){
    if(ci>=chunks.length) return Promise.resolve();
    var boundary='makor_batch_'+ci+'_'+attempt;
    var body=chunks[ci].map(function(ev,j){
      return '--'+boundary+'\r\nContent-Type: application/http\r\nContent-ID: <item'+j+'>\r\n\r\n'+
        'POST /calendar/v3/calendars/'+encodeURIComponent(calId)+'/events\r\nContent-Type: application/json\r\n\r\n'+
        JSON.stringify(ev)+'\r\n';
    }).join('')+'--'+boundary+'--';
    return fetch('https://www.googleapis.com/batch/calendar/v3',{
      method:'POST',
      headers:{'Authorization':'Bearer '+token,'Content-Type':'multipart/mixed; boundary='+boundary},
      body:body
    }).then(function(r){
      if(r.status===401||r.status===403){ var e=new Error('auth'); e.status=r.status; throw e; }
      return r.text();
    }).then(function(text){
      var failed=(text.match(/"error"/g)||[]).length;
      if(failed>0 && attempt<2){
        return new Promise(function(res){setTimeout(res,4000);}).then(function(){ return send(ci,attempt+1); });
      }
      done+=chunks[ci].length;
      onProgress(done,events.length);
      return new Promise(function(res){setTimeout(res,2500);}).then(function(){ return send(ci+1,0); });
    });
  }
  return send(0,0);
}

function fetchIndex(order){
  return fetch('/plan-index-'+order+'.json').then(function(r){return r.json();})
    .then(function(d){ return (Array.isArray(d)&&d.length)?d:SAMPLE; })
    .catch(function(){ return SAMPLE; });
}

function readCfgFromDescription(desc){
  try{
    var m=String(desc||'').match(/Config:\s*(\{[\s\S]*\})/);
    return m?JSON.parse(m[1]):null;
  }catch(e){ return null; }
}

function storedCalId(sess){
  try{ return (sess&&sess.user&&sess.user.user_metadata&&sess.user.user_metadata.makor_gcal_id)||localStorage.getItem('makor_gcal_id')||null; }catch(e){ return null; }
}
function storeCalId(id){
  try{ localStorage.setItem('makor_gcal_id',id); }catch(e){}
  try{ window.makorClient.auth.updateUser({data:{makor_gcal_id:id}}); }catch(e){}
}

function gcalAuth(){
  var tries=0;
  try{ tries=+(sessionStorage.getItem('makor_gcal_tries')||0); }catch(e){}
  if(tries>=2){
    try{ sessionStorage.removeItem('makor_gcal_tries'); }catch(e){}
    gsay('Google did not grant Makor calendar access. Press the button to try again, and on the Google screen make sure the calendar permission checkbox is ticked.');
    return;
  }
  try{ sessionStorage.setItem('makor_gcal_tries',String(tries+1)); }catch(e){}
  try{ localStorage.setItem('makor_gcal_pending',JSON.stringify(cfgFromState())); }catch(e){}
  window.makorClient.auth.signInWithOAuth({ provider:'google', options:{
    scopes:GCAL_SCOPE,
    redirectTo:location.origin+'/plan/?gcal=resume',
    queryParams:{ include_granted_scopes:'true' }
  }});
}

function findMakorCalendar(sess,token){
  var known=storedCalId(sess);
  var viaGet=known?gapi('/calendars/'+encodeURIComponent(known),'GET',null,token).catch(function(){return null;}):Promise.resolve(null);
  return viaGet.then(function(cal){
    if(cal&&cal.id) return cal;
    return gapi('/users/me/calendarList','GET',null,token).then(function(list){
      var hit=((list&&list.items)||[]).filter(function(c){return c.summary===CAL_SUMMARY;})[0];
      return hit?gapi('/calendars/'+encodeURIComponent(hit.id),'GET',null,token).catch(function(){return hit;}):null;
    }).catch(function(){ return null; });
  });
}

function listPlanEvents(calId,token,pageToken,acc){
  var q='/calendars/'+encodeURIComponent(calId)+'/events?maxResults=2500&fields=nextPageToken,items(start,extendedProperties)'+(pageToken?'&pageToken='+encodeURIComponent(pageToken):'');
  return gapi(q,'GET',null,token).then(function(res){
    acc=acc.concat((res&&res.items)||[]);
    if(res&&res.nextPageToken) return listPlanEvents(calId,token,res.nextPageToken,acc);
    return acc;
  });
}

function gcalProgress(done,total){ gsay('Adding your readings: '+done+' of '+total+' entries placed...'); }

function gcalCreateAndFill(token,cfg){
  gsay('Creating your Makor reading plan calendar...');
  return fetchIndex(cfg.order).then(function(list){
    return gapi('/calendars','POST',{
      summary:CAL_SUMMARY,
      description:'Your Makor reading plan, managed from makor.co.za/plan. Delete this calendar to remove the whole plan. Config: '+JSON.stringify(cfg),
      timeZone:userTz()
    },token).then(function(cal){
      storeCalId(cal.id);
      var startDay=new Date((cfg.start||new Date().toISOString().slice(0,10))+'T00:00:00');
      var evs=scheduleEvents(list,startDay,cfg);
      return gcalBatchInsert(cal.id,evs,token,gcalProgress).then(function(){
        try{ sessionStorage.removeItem('makor_gcal_tries'); }catch(e){}
        savePlanLocal(cfg); showPlanCard(cfg);
        gsay('Done. '+list.length+' studies are on your Google Calendar in the "Makor reading plan" calendar. As new studies are published, press the button again and we will add them.');
      });
    });
  });
}

function gcalSync(cal,token){
  gsay('You already have a Makor plan calendar. Checking for newly published studies...');
  var cfg=readCfgFromDescription(cal.description)||cfgFromState();
  return fetchIndex(cfg.order).then(function(list){
    return listPlanEvents(cal.id,token,null,[]).then(function(items){
      var have={}, lastDate=null;
      items.forEach(function(ev){
        var urls=ev.extendedProperties&&ev.extendedProperties.private&&ev.extendedProperties.private.makorUrls;
        if(urls) urls.split(' ').forEach(function(u){ have[u]=1; });
        var d=ev.start&&(ev.start.dateTime||ev.start.date);
        if(d&&(!lastDate||d>lastDate)) lastDate=d;
      });
      var missing=list.filter(function(x){ return !have[x.url]; });
      if(!missing.length){
        try{ sessionStorage.removeItem('makor_gcal_tries'); }catch(e){}
        savePlanLocal(cfg); showPlanCard(cfg);
        gsay('Your calendar already has every committed study ('+list.length+'). Check back after new studies are published.');
        return;
      }
      var startDay=lastDate?new Date(String(lastDate).slice(0,10)+'T00:00:00'):new Date();
      startDay.setDate(startDay.getDate()+1);
      var evs=scheduleEvents(missing,startDay,cfg);
      gsay('Adding '+missing.length+' newly published studies to your calendar...');
      return gcalBatchInsert(cal.id,evs,token,gcalProgress).then(function(){
        try{ sessionStorage.removeItem('makor_gcal_tries'); }catch(e){}
        savePlanLocal(cfg); showPlanCard(cfg);
        gsay('Done. '+missing.length+' new studies added, continuing at your usual pace and times.');
      });
    });
  });
}

function gcalRun(cfg){
  var btn=document.getElementById('gcal'); btn.disabled=true;
  gsay('Connecting to Google...');
  window.makorClient.auth.getSession().then(function(r){
    var sess=r.data&&r.data.session;
    var token=sess&&sess.provider_token;
    if(!token){ gcalAuth(); return; }
    return findMakorCalendar(sess,token).then(function(cal){
      if(cal&&cal.id){ storeCalId(cal.id); return gcalSync(cal,token); }
      return gcalCreateAndFill(token,cfg||cfgFromState());
    }).catch(function(e){
      if(e&&(e.status===401||e.status===403)){ gcalAuth(); return; }
      gsay('Something went wrong talking to Google Calendar. Try again in a minute, or use the file download below.');
    });
  }).then(function(){ btn.disabled=false; }).catch(function(){ btn.disabled=false; });
}

document.getElementById('gcal').onclick=function(){
  if(!window.makorClient){ gsay('One moment, the page is still loading, then press the button again.'); return; }
  gcalRun(cfgFromState());
};

// Returning from the Google consent screen: restore choices and continue.
// We resume whenever a pending request exists, not only when the ?gcal=resume
// marker survives the round trip, because Supabase falls back to the site
// homepage when /plan/ is missing from its redirect allow-list; the user
// then returns here and the plan still completes.
(function(){
  var marked=location.search.indexOf('gcal=resume')>=0;
  var cfg=null;
  try{ cfg=JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('makor_gcal_pending')||'null'); }catch(e){}
  if(!marked && !cfg) return;
  if(marked){ try{ history.replaceState(null,'',location.pathname); }catch(e){} }
  function go(){
    window.makorClient.auth.getSession().then(function(r){
      var sess=r.data&&r.data.session;
      if(!(sess&&sess.provider_token)){
        // No Google token in hand: a stale pending flag, clear it quietly.
        try{ localStorage.removeItem('makor_gcal_pending'); }catch(e){}
        if(marked) gsay('The Google sign in did not complete. Press the button to try again.');
        return;
      }
      try{ localStorage.removeItem('makor_gcal_pending'); }catch(e){}
      if(cfg) applyCfg(cfg);
      gsay('Finishing your Google sign in...');
      gcalRun(cfg||cfgFromState());
    });
  }
  if(window.makorClient) go();
  else window.addEventListener('makor-auth',go,{once:true});
})();
</script>
